comment: Collison (SAC) cleanly strips the ball from Lin (CHA) prior to any incidental foot to foot contact.
Daniels (CHA) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact that does not affect Collison's (SAC) layup attempt.
Hawes (SAC) makes contact with the ball after it hits the backboard.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court of a goaltending violation by Hawes (CHA) was confirmed.
Hawes (CHA) sets the screen on Gay (SAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Collison (SAC) makes contact with the ball causing Walker (CHA) to momentarily lose possession prior to moving his pivot foot.
Collison (SAC) undercuts Walker (CHA) causing him to fall to the floor after securing the loose ball.
Walker (CHA) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Cousins (SAC) prior to any incidental contact with his arm.
Cousins (SAC) makes contact with Walker (CHA) while reaching in for the steal from behind.
Cousins (SAC) firms up as he sets the screen on Daniels (CHA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Cauley-Stein (SAC) obtains a legal guarding position prior to absorbing the contact from Walker (CHA) who initiates the contact.
Gay (SAC) sets the screen on Hawes (CHA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Walker (CHA) was confirmed.
Hawes (CHA) makes contact with Cousins' (SAC) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Cauley-Stein (SAC) trips Walker (SAC) and affects his RSBQ on the drive.
Collison (SAC) is maintaining his balance and does not disconcert Walker (CHA) during the second FT attempt.
Rondo (SAC) and Lin (CHA) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Cousins (SAC) makes contact with Lin's (CHA) arm affecting his ability to complete the pass.
Williams (CHA) makes contact with Cousins' (SAC) body during his alley-oop dunk.
Lin (CHA) makes contact with the ball prior to any incidental contact with Cousins' (SAC) arm during rebounding.
Lin (CHA) makes contact with Cousins (SAC) that affects his ability to secure the loose ball.
Kaminsky (CHA) legally contests Cousins' (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court of a 24 second violation was confirmed.
Walker (CHA) maintains his pivot foot after ending his dribble.
Although Hansbrough (CHA) cleanly strips the ball with his right hand, he grabs and holds Cousins' (SAC) right arm affecting his movement to the basket.
Kaminsky (CHA) and Cousins (SAC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Kaminsky (CHA) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Cousins' (SAC) driving layup attempt.
Cousins (SAC) and Kaminsky (CHA) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Cauley-Stein (SAC) makes contact with Walker's (CHA) body that affects his driving layup attempt.
LHH shows that Kaminsky (CHA) maintains legal guarding position and legally contests Cousins' (SAC) layup attempt. As Cousins attempts the layup he initiates any contact with Hairston's (CHA) arm.
Gay (SAC) maintains legal guarding position and Cauley-Stein (SAC) cleanly blocks Walker's (CHA) driving layup attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined there was a clock malfunction that caused the clock to continue to run after the 24 second violation. The officials placed 00:01.6 on the clock and Sacramento was awarded possession.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Anderson (SAC) stumbles to the ground and makes incidental contact with Walker (CHA) that does not affect his RSBQ.
LHH shows that Hairston (CHA) makes contact with Gay's (SAC) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Walker (CHA) makes contact with Gay's (SAC) face during his jump shot attempt.
Rondo (SAC) walks under Daniels (CHA) and does not allow him the room to land following his jump shot attempt.
Cousins (SAC) and Kaminsky (CHA) briefly engage and separate as they attempt to establish post position.

LATR and L-Slash show Cousins (SAC) attempts to create space after securing the rebound by initiating contact with Kaminsky, who is in a legal guarding position after the rebound is secured, and he dislodges him from his position.

Collison (SAC) controls the ball, which should lead to a reset of the shot clock. The clock does not reset and Lin (CHA) attempts a 3 point field goal to beat the clock. The officials stop play and communicate, determining that the clock should be reset and Charlotte regain possession.
LATR shows that Hairston (CHA) pushes Cauley-Stein (SAC) as he attempts to set the screen causing him to continue moving into Walker (CHA).
Casspi (SAC) and Kaminsky (CHA) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding and Kaminsky causes the ball to go OOB.
Lin's (CHA) grabs Cauley-Stein's (SAC) right arm affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Lin (CHA) legally contests Belinelli's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Cauley-Stein (SAC) grabs and pulls Hairston's (CHA) arm affecting his ability to secure the loose ball.
Rondo (SAC) cleanly strips the ball from Walker (CHA).
RHH shows that Cauley-Stein (SAC) maintains legal guarding position while Casspi (SAC) cleanly blocks Kaminsky's (CHA) driving layup attempt.
Kaminsky (CHA) sets the screen on Collison (SAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Daniels (CHA) moves his pivot foot prior to releasing the jump shot.
Walker (CHA) legally contests Collison's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Daniels (CHA) and Casspi (SAC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
